title: For Sale:  SAWN OFF WINCHESTER MODEL 370 20GAUGE
postcontent:
Found this old girl in a barn tucked up into some rafters. It was beat to hell, the barrel was rusted up and the action wouldn't open. But after soaking it in some break away it popped open fine. Next I tore the gun completely apart and roughed up all the rust I could and neutralized it with baking soda, then heating the barrel up I then soaked it in motor oil. ( also known as the browning process). So now the barrel is a pretty cool dark brown antique color, instead of blued steel.( you can see the brown and blue in one of my pics bec the bottom wasn't rusted) Next the stock and foreend were sanded down smooth and stained a much darker color. Then I cut the barrel down, not a hack job either I used a pipe cutter unlike most who just use a hack saw.

The barrel measures 19 7/8" which is way over the legal length minimum of 18.5" in MI. Best part is this can handle 3" loads so would be a great home defense gun, or for rabbits in tight brush like I was using it. With 6 shot I was knocking rabbits around out to 40+ yards. Ive also shot slugs out of it and surprisingly it does decent at 20-30yds without a front bead. ( never got around to welding one on)

The sling is just an old belt I screwed into the stock. Gun functions great, and ejects shells good. 

$50 firm on the price
